def calculate_share(df, column):
    return df[column].value_counts(normalize=True) * 100  #

def prepare_user_stats(df):
    #   
    user_stats = df.groupby("user_id").agg(
        avg_orders_per_user=("order_id", "count"),   #  
        avg_days_between_orders=("days_since_prev", "mean")  #    
    ).reset_index()

    return user_stats

In[69]:
def perform_hypothesis_test(sample1, sample2, alternative='greater'):
    results = {}
    
    #  U- -
    u_stat, p_value = stats.mannwhitneyu(
        sample1, 
        sample2, 
        alternative=alternative,
        method='auto'
    )
    
    results['mannwhitney'] = {
        'statistic': u_stat,
        'pvalue': p_value,
        'alternative': alternative
    }
    
    return results
